sentences: Saeko Zōgō (藏合 紗恵子, Zōgō Saeko, born August 13, 1984) is a Japanese actress, voice actress and singer from Tsuyama, Okayama Prefecture, Japan.
She is affiliated with Production Ace.
Her major roles are: Ichiyon (M14) in Upotte!!, Nadeshiko Sōma in Isuca, Freon Flamel in Sky Wizards Academy, Sōji Okita in Dai-Shogun - Great Revolution, and Shiori Itsuka in Date A Live II.
She and fellow voice actress Kaori Sadohara were part of a duo called Two-Formula who sang songs on Isuca and Noucome.
She announced her marriage on May 21, 2017.
"Reach for Light" (Nippon Columbia, February 12, 2014) – Reached number 111 at Oricon.
Nagareda Project (Nippon Columbia, April 29, 2015) – Reached number 92 at Oricon.
"Somebody to Love" (5pb records, January 28, 2015) – ending theme song from Isuca.
"Taiyou to Tsuki no CROSS" (太陽と月のCROSS) (5pb records, November 27, 2013) – theme song from Noucome.
